CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1960, pg. B4, reads: "New District Manager - Staff managers and clerical personnel of the Pittsburgh branch of North Carolina Mutual Life Insurance Company pose with the company's new branch manager, Harry A. Carter, far right, front row. Mr. Carter replaced J. D. Lewis Sr., who resigned recently.  Front row, left to right, are: Offerell Johnson, Homer Boykin, Fred Ables, Maude Hawkins, Isabelle Hawkins, Odile Posey Bennett, Winona Hall, Emma L. Carroll, J. A. Griffith, Richard Robinson and Mr. Carter.  Back row: Richard Hill, Eugene Carter, Charles Prioleau, James Charles, "Ted" Thomas, Louise Boykins, Samuel Mosley, Milton Jones, William Rawlings, and Earl McGuire. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of men and women, including front row, left to right: Offerell Johnson, Homer Boykin, Fred Ables, Maude Hawkins, Isabelle Hawkins, Odile Posey Bennett, Winona Hall, Emma L. Carroll, J. A. Griffith, Richard Robinson, and District Manager Harry A. Carter;  back row: Richard Hill, Eugene Carter, Charles Prioleau, James Charles, "Ted" Thomas, Louise Boykins, Samuel Mosley, Milton Jones, William Rawlings, and Earl McGuire, standing in front of Pittsburgh District North Carolina Mutual Life Insurance Company, 2018 Centre Avenue, with snow piled on curb in foreground, Hill District
